[According to both reports, the disease in Romania has been observed, recorded, and laboratory confirmed in cattle, in contrast to recent reports on bluetongue epizootics in Greece, Bulgaria, the Former Yugoslavian Republic of Macedonia, and Turkey, where the disease has been affecting almost exclusively sheep and where the serotype has been found to be BTV-4. Traditionally, this serotype has long been known to cause clinical disease primarily in sheep, while in cattle, a species readily infected by the same vector, the infection remained subclinical in the vast majority of cases.

The (1969-2014) list of BTV-4 isolates in the dsRNA virus collection at IAH Pirbright includes details on the species of the affected, sampled animals and other data, e.g. date and country of origin; see at http://www.reoviridae.org/dsRNA_virus_proteins/ReoID/btv-4.htm#BUL2014/14.

The result of serotyping of the BT virus circulating in Romania is anticipated with great interest. - Mods.AS/CRD

